   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> CS</span><hr size=1> Not sure how it is on your server but on Mith Marr CS is definately a free for all.  Occasionally you'll come across people who will honor you being at the otters first as there really isn't more than enough to support 2 ppl tops.  As for the wyvrens and drakes they have always been first come first serve. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If your having problems getting spawns learn to pull the tower it's hardly ever *camped*.  <br>
<br>
Alphie Bits<br>
GNOME wizzy<br>
Mith Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usorasha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorasha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/21/02 1:51:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cobalt Scar</span><hr size=1> I agree that Cobalt Scar has become whiner's retreat. Not a day goes by that some n00b who could never have made it to CS pre-Luclin has just discovered the place and is offended that 5 people in the zone means there is little to kill. I've taken the hard line with them, I advise them there are no camps in CS thank you very much and there hasn't been for the many levels I've killed wyverns, drakes and otters. They also need reminted that its considered extremely bad manners to tag that wyvern that is chasing me, as that could be considered KSing. Someone even wanted to yell at me for swearing so I told him if it offended him he has this cool thing called a FILTER.<br>
<br>
Now, if someone says, hey, would you mind if I/we take these 2 and you can have those 2. That's different. I'm happy to share and make it work. But I paid my dues running thru Kael hoping Invis wouldn't drop, with sweaty palms and all, to get my WL key right before making a death defying run through Skysrhine (again hoping invis wouldn't drop). But these mid 40 babies who pop in LFG (/boggle) can just leave my zone for all I care. I can make VI's &quot;play nice rules&quot; work to my favor in this one. And its always fun to snicker at them when they aggro Azureake or Yvolcarn for the first time. <br>
<br>
Sorasha<br>
56th Evoker<br>
Povar Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 8:08:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cobalt Scar</span><hr size=1> On Prexus CS does have an established &quot;camp&quot; check.  The otters.  Most everyone i've seen will observe this as a camp but the rest of the things in the zone that move are FFA.  Hehe  every once in a while someone will try to clain the single spawn seachest.  So i just pull it and kite it underwater a few times and explain to them that the last patch extended the spawn time to 30 minutes.  Fishbone earring has changed the way i play greatly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66366>Orsmo Xlorr 52 Lvl Wizard</A>


