</table> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukunayan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kunayan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/23/02 7:15:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cobalt Scar</span><hr size=1> A little off topic but...<br>
<br>
I was kiting spirocs in TD the other day and I kept having one or two birds disappearing from my quad. <br>
<br>
I could never found who took it though as I still had 2 or 3 mobs chasing me. There were not any extra as the Spirocs were camped pretty heavily. Finally one time I had 4 behind me and I had just snared them and when I tried to cast CoF I got out of range. I turned around and one spiroc was walking up. I ran back and sure enough a group of three were killing my spirocs. So I memmed IC real quick and KS'ed all three back. You could tell that these were mine cause when I IC'd one it started walking toward me at a slow speed snared. I then commented to them that they should pay attention to what they were pulling.  <br>
<br>
I dont think I lost another Spiroc that I had pulled after that though.  <br>
<br>
I think if they are up then they are free for all. If they want to kill them then they should be able to kill them as they appear otherwise it is just waisted xp.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usherekhaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shere Khaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/23/02 9:53:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cobalt Scar</span><hr size=1> Biggest problem I have had was with druids and not melee. and it wasn't a problem to me at all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I pull (like most wizards) with my flux staff so if spawns are contested I keep an eye out and run past and pull them with my beautiful agro very soon after pop. Mean while druids have to run up to one, cast ensnare, then another one etc. I have received a couple of angry tells from druids accusing me of KS'ing because they were just about to snare that one.<br>
<br>
Bare in mind that I don't do this intentionally. If I see a druid infront of a wyvern obviously pulling I won't interfere out of courtesy.<br>
<br>
Maelific <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umajique.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Majique</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/29/02 12:48:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cobalt Scar</span><hr size=1> I am a lvl 53 Wizard on The Rathe server.  I have always been very happy with the CS zone as a place to go to get some peace and some good solo exp.  Since the release of Luclin and the very BAD decision of verant to remove the need of the tooth to port there it is almost impossible to do, especially at peak times.  CS is and has always been a free for all zone.  There are no camps; at least not when it comes to the Wyvernn.  Furthermore, it is actually very dangerous to others for KOS ppl and ppl that just dont know about the zone to be running around there.  I had some idiot pull a Siren on to the beach the other day.  I suppose that person must have died.. Next thing I know a Siren is beating on me.  Charmed me once but i just barely managed to get away.  <br>
<br>
Long story short Verant has managed to ruin an excellent zone that ppl more or less had to earn the right to get to before.  Kinda sucks.<br>
<br>
